This paper focuses on change impact analysis in object-oriented software, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The proposed algorithm, LCIP, is a learning algorithm that learns from past impacts to predict future impacts, which suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions code mutations, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Additionally, the use of strongly tested Java software applications suggests a software development (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, the use of a learning algorithm for prediction suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
